$\begin{align}
5^2\cdot 5^5&=5^{2+5}
\\\\
&=5^7
\end{align}$

This follows from the general rule $x^m\cdot x^n=x^{m+n}$. Note that the powers have the same base.

We can also see this is correct by expanding the powers.

$\begin{align}
5^2\cdot 5^5&=\underbrace{5\cdot 5}_\text{2 times}\cdot\underbrace{5\cdot 5\cdot 5\cdot 5\cdot 5}_\text{5 times}
\\\\\\
&=\underbrace{5\cdot 5\cdot 5\cdot 5\cdot 5\cdot 5\cdot 5}_\text{7 times}
\\\\
&=5^7
\end{align}$

